# Repository Delta

A **Repository Delta** records what actually changed after implementation. It is the durable trace that lets future maintainers or agents understand completed work without inspecting every commit.

It captures the answers to four questions:

- What changed?
- Which directive, issue, or request did it fulfill?
- How was it verified?
- Did the implementation depart from the original plan?

## Use this for

- Completed changes whose provenance should remain visible.
- Work that fulfilled one or more directives.
- Changes where verification, deviations, or follow-up context matter.

Do not use it for planned or ongoing work, open questions, or high-level goals.

## Minimum record

| Section | Captures |
|---|---|
| `# Fulfilled directives` | Links to the directive, issue, request, or decision that caused the work. |
| `# Change summary` | What changed in the project. |
| `# Verification` | Tests, checks, review notes, or observations proving the change works. |
| `# Deviations` | Optional differences from the original directive or expected path. |
| `# Related decisions` | Optional links to decisions that informed the change. |

## Schema

```yaml
---
type: Repository Delta
title: <short name>
description: <one-line summary>
tags: [delta, <domain>]
timestamp: <ISO 8601 datetime>
status: <completed | superseded | reverted>
---

# Fulfilled directives

# Change summary

# Verification

# Deviations

# Related decisions
```
